    	<section id="overview" class="heading-section content-section section__anchor--sticky">
			<p>In the first two years of this course, you will be introduced to core material relevant to all biology programmes, such as animal and plant biology, molecular biology, cell biology and genetics.</p>  
			<p>In your third year, you will begin studying more specialised modules that will prepare you for your Honours degree. In fourth year, you will continue specific research in your chosen area through student-led, enquiry-based learning.</p> 
			<p>At St Andrews, you will have access to high-tech equipment, laboratories and expertise to help you learn and to develop your skillset as a modern biologist.</p>  
			<p>Centres of research within the School of Biology offer you the experience to work alongside experts while developing your own research in your Honours years. Find out more about <a href="https://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/biology/research/centres/">biology centres and institutes</a> at St Andrews.</p> 
